						               													<description>Greater Evil is a strategic version of the game &amp;ldquo;Bullshit,&amp;rdquo; with a political twist. Players shamelessly pander, lie, call each other liars, and play Presidential Candidates in a reckless fight to win the support of campaign Backers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each Backer on the board is susceptible to different kinds of Rhetoric cards, which come in five categories: Promises, Exaggerations, Sweet Talk, Facts, and Lies. Players play Rhetoric cards face down, but announce their play to the table (e.g., &amp;quot;two promises&amp;quot;). You can lie about what you're playing, but be warned: if another player calls you out as a liar, they'll get to steal your cards for themselves.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Presidential Candidate cards such as Asshat, Patriotic Pony, Shit Burger, Politibot 2016, and Jesus Toast can turn the tide. Their special powers can attack your opponents or save yourself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Win a Backer and collect its points by being the first to play enough Rhetoric cards on it. The player with the most points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
